work.heading: helping you find  the best tutors
work.title: tutors.com
work.description_text: we helped tutors.com develop their platform in their early stages. they had a ton of UX issues they needed to solve from the start with the goal of creating the best online tutor platform.

content.heading: the solution
content.text:
we solved the UX issues by facilitating multiple user studies and testing before launching the final product. 

we helped develop their web and mobile platforms, ensuring cross platform capabilities for their users. 

their platform now gets over 100,000 visitors each month.

work.heading: providing gps  for your money
work.title: fitbux
work.description_text: prior to us working with fitbux, they had a great piece of technology but a terrible and confusing interface. they were able to build up a high five figure user base, but their ui was in such rough shape that was causing frustration for the users and hurting scalabiliy for the company.

text.paragraph: we took what was working well with the previous logo and refined its form to work on a broader scale of applications and sizes.

thanks to the new redesign, the users involved in the testing were blown away by the ease of use. fitbux is now able to leverage their great technology with a clean ui to help them on their multi million dollar raise to help scale their product.
post completion of the rebranded identity and web application, we built a mobile app to help users keep up with their financial plan and manage transactions.

work.heading: a modern look for a traditional industry
work.title: orion electric
work.description_text: prior to us working with fitbux, they had a great piece of technology but a terrible and confusing interface. they were able to build up a high five figure user base, but their ui was in such rough shape that was causing frustration for the users and hurting scalabiliy for the company.

text.paragraph: orion electric was having the same problem that most traditional service companies were having - blending in with outdated branding and not appealing to their target audience. this created the goal to rebrand and appeal to higher end electrical clients and contracts.

after diving into orion's target audience and understanding their competitive landscape, we were able to put together a strategy to help differentiate them from other electrical companies and appeal to their more luxury clientele.
we then put together a tactical roadmap on how they can use their new visual identity to create an entirely new and original look from any other electrical company in the country.

home.cta: leading digital agency with solid design and development expertise. we specialize in defining the user ex and build readymade websites, mobile applications, and elaborate online business services.
home.services_text:
our name is a play on words of our design philosophy - get to the core of the users main or primary experience, then create your product around it. we take on every project and problem with an open mind, curious spirit and without preconceived ideas.

we love crafting beautiful, smart and inspired work that is focused on a business goals and their customers. we do this across multiple touch points to help organizations achieve their goals.

content.heading: our services and capabilities
content.text: we love crafting beautiful, smart and inspired work that is focused on a business goals and their customers. we do this across multiple touch points to help organizations achieve their goals.

agency.heading: the point where art  and tech meet

text.paragraph: originally a small modest agency known as mainello montage founded  in 2017, mainux  has gone on to define itself as a leader in user experience design for startups and early stage saas (software as a service) products.

our team of talented designers, developers, and strategists have worked with companies both small and large including blue nile, business insider, and much more.   our mission is simple  consistently deliver ideas and work that matters and exceeds client expectations.

content.quote: you have to start with the customer experience and work your way back to technology.

content.heading: our approach
content.text:
everything we do at mainux consists of providing solutions for intended users. this can be applied to products, business models, branding, and especially digital solutions.

we put the needs of the user at the center of everything we create, which is the most powerful way to start and finish each project.
